<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="69" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d69">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 493.11/471.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Chinese Legation</gloss> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <p rend="center">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">memorandum</hi>.</p>
                        <p>In reply to a telegram from the Legation asking what disposition is to be
                            made of the balance of deposits refundable to China upon the remitted
                            portion of the indemnity, the Foreign Office cabled instruction to the
                            Legation to receive such balance in the same manner as it did last
                            August.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <dateline rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Chinese Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-20"><hi rend="italic">January 20, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>